        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">This letter is a version of the draft <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9485F.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. C. Marshall, 8 June [1874]</ref>. For possible recipients see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. T. Thiselton-Dyer, 9 June 1874</ref> and n. 3. The amanuensis, possibly <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref>, made the copy from a version in <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> hand; he follows her consistent misspelling of <hi rend="italic">Pinguicula</hi> (butterwort) as ‘Pinguicola’ (see for example, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. T. Thiselton-Dyer, 9 June 1874</ref>). <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> version, now in DAR 59.1: 88, was used as the basis for the draft <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9514F.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Ralfs, [after 25 June 1874]</ref>; CD marked the alterations for the letter to Ralfs directly onto her copy.</note>
